{"tipType":"windowShade","windowShade":{"windowShadeType":"teacherTip","layout":"mediaLeft","initialOpenState":true,"content":"*You can open and close this tip, and other teacher tips in this module, by clicking on the blue Teacher Tip button above.*

This module has been designed to use research-based practices in science education, particularly Ambitious Science Teaching. Questions on this page may appear to ask students about things with which they are unfamiliar or have had no prior experience as part of a science class. It is okay if students' explanations are incomplete or incorrect. The goal is to set the foundation upon which students can build their ideas.
